# HeroUI v3 Usage Rules

## Setup (installed)
```
@heroui/react@3.0.0-rc.1
@heroui/styles@3.0.0-rc.1
framer-motion (peer dependency)
```

`src/styles/global.css`:
```css
@import 'tailwindcss';
@import '@heroui/styles';
```

No Provider wrapper needed — HeroUI v3 is CSS-first, there is no `<HeroUIProvider>`.

---

## Core Rules
- If HeroUI has an equivalent component → **use HeroUI**, do not write a custom one
- Only write custom components when app-specific logic or visuals are needed (see `shared-components.mdc`)
- Always import from **individual packages** — never use the barrel `@heroui/react`

---

## UI Wrapper Rule — MANDATORY

HeroUI v3 uses compound component patterns (e.g. `Switch.Control + Switch.Thumb`, `Checkbox.Control + Checkbox.Indicator`).
**Never use HeroUI compound components directly in feature code.**
Instead, always wrap them once in `src/components/ui/` and import the wrapper everywhere.

```
src/components/ui/
  Button.tsx           ← wraps @heroui/react/button
  Checkbox.tsx         ← wraps @heroui/react/checkbox (Control + Indicator + Content)
  InfoTooltip.tsx      ← wraps @heroui/react/tooltip (Trigger + Content + arrow)
  PillGroup.tsx        ← reusable pill button group (uses InfoTooltip)
  SegmentedControl.tsx ← segmented button bar (native, no HeroUI)
  Slider.tsx           ← wraps @heroui/react/slider (Track + Fill + Thumb sized)
  Switch.tsx           ← wraps @heroui/react/switch (Control + Thumb)
  Tabs.tsx             ← custom tab bar + content via render prop
```

**Rules:**
- **NEVER** import `@heroui/react/switch`, `@heroui/react/checkbox`, `@heroui/react/slider`, `@heroui/react/tooltip` directly in feature components
- **ALWAYS** import from `@/components/ui/` instead
- If a new HeroUI compound component is needed → create a wrapper in `src/components/ui/` first

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG — compound boilerplate leaks into feature code
import { Switch } from '@heroui/react/switch';
<Switch isSelected={v} onChange={set}>
  <Switch.Control><Switch.Thumb /></Switch.Control>
</Switch>

// ✅ CORRECT — clean wrapper
import { Switch } from '@/components/ui/Switch';
<Switch isSelected={v} onChange={set} label="Upscale" />
```

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
import { Button } from '@heroui/react/button';
import { Input } from '@heroui/react/input';

// ❌ WRONG — barrel import increases bundle size
import { Button, Input } from '@heroui/react';
```

