## Framer Motion — animations

```tsx
import { motion } from 'framer-motion';

// Fade in on mount
<motion.div initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 16 }} animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }} transition={{ duration: 0.3 }}>
  <GlassCard>...</GlassCard>
</motion.div>

// Stagger list items
const container = { hidden: {}, show: { transition: { staggerChildren: 0.07 } } };
const item = { hidden: { opacity: 0, y: 10 }, show: { opacity: 1, y: 0 } };

<motion.div variants={container} initial="hidden" animate="show">
  {items.map(i => <motion.div key={i.id} variants={item}>{/* ... */}</motion.div>)}
</motion.div>
```

Use for: page transitions, card reveals, before/after slider handle, stagger feature grids.
Do NOT use for: loading spinners (→ HeroUI `Spinner`), simple hover colors (→ Tailwind `transition`).

---

## Do Not
- Do NOT override HeroUI styles with `!important`
- Do NOT write custom Button / Input / Modal / Table — use HeroUI
- Do NOT import from the `@heroui/react` barrel when an individual package is available
